CategoryStepper

	Version 1.5
	Copyright Â© 2007-2008 MinuteElectron.
	Licensed under the GNU General Public License 2.0 or later.

The CategoryStepper extension displays a category stepper box allowing one to
navigate forward and backwards alphabetically through one or more categories a
page is in, as specified via a MediaWiki: namespace page or the
$wgCategoryStepper configuration variable.

== Requirements ==

The CategoryStepper extension requires MediaWiki 1.11.0 or later.

== Installation ==

1. Place the CategoryStepper.php source code into
   extensions/CategoryStepper/CategoryStepper.php.
2. Place the CategoryStepper.i18n.php source code into
   extensions/CategoryStepper/CategoryStepper.i18n.php.
3. If desired place the CategoryStepper.css source code into
   skins/CategoryStepper.css.
4. Add require_once( "$IP/extensions/CategoryStepper/CategoryStepper.php" ); to
   LocalSettings.php.
5. Enjoy!

Installation can be verified through the [[Special:Version]] page on the wiki.

== Using the extension ==

CategoryStepper adds a box to the bottom of the content area on pages which are
in a specified category.  Categories can be configured either via using the
$wgCategoryStepper configuration variable or by mofifying the page
MediaWiki:categorystepper.

Fill the $wgCategoryStepper variable with a list of category names to stepper
box titles; e.g.
$wgCategoryStepper[ "Astronauts" ] = "Astronauts Box Title";

Alternatively set the $wgCategoryStepper variable to false and use the
MediaWiki:Categorystepper page to set options; e.g.

LocalSettings.php:
	$wgCategoryStepper = false;
MediaWiki:Categorystepper:
	* Astronauts|Astronauts Box Title

== Change log ==

Version 1.1
2008-01-19
	Original version.

Version 1.2
2008-01-20
	Added missing space in i18n file.

Version 1.3
2008-02-16
	No longer render on edit, protect or delete pages.
	Allow modification of categories and title via the
		MediaWiki:categorystepper page.

Version 1.4
2008-02-17
	The second parameter of each row on the	MediaWiki:categorystepper page is
		now optional and defaults to the first parameter.

Version 1.5
2008-02-26
	Default wikitable-like styling is now included and can optionally be used,
		or overridden via MediaWiki:Common.css or the individual skins CSS
		MediaWiki namespace pages.
	README added.
	Function wfCategoryStepper renamed to efCategoryStepper.
	ltrim() now used instead of preg_replace().

== Feedback ==

Bugs and feature requests should be reported via MediaZilla
<http://bugzilla.wikimedia.org/> and placed in the 'MediaWiki extensions'
product under the CategoryStepper component.  Alternatively send an e-mail to
<minuteelectron@googlemail.com> with any comments or suggestions, all are
welcome.
